wikipedia_page.main: Gary Jennings (born 21 February 1972) is a male British former hurdler. He competed in the men's 400 metres hurdles at the 1996 Summer Olympics. He represented England in the 400 metres hurdles event, at the 1998 Commonwealth Games in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.

response: Yeovil Olympiads Athletics Club, founded in 1969, has produced many international athletes. The first was Eric Berry, who came 6th in the 1973 European Juniors in the hammer event. Olympians who started with the club include Max Robertson and Gary Jennings, both 400-metre hurdlers.
